Sentencas: A new cubic perovskite oxide, SrCo0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-delta(SCFN), is investigated as a cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Characterization of SrCo0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-δ cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: XRD results show that there are no serious reactions between SCFN and Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9(SDC) except a slight peak shift.

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of the SCFN sample reaches a maximum 304 S cm(-1) at 350 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Characterization of SrCo0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-δ cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In order to optimize thermal expansion coefficients (TECs) and electrochemical performance of the SCFN cathode, we fabricate SCFN-xSDC (x = 0, 20, 30, 40, 50, 60, wt%) composite cathodes.
Titulo: Characterization of SrCo0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-δ cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The thermal expansion behavior shows that the TECs value of SCFN cathode decreases greatly with SDC addition.
Titulo: Characterization of SrCo0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-δ cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SDC addition reduces the polarization resistance, and the lowest polarization resistance 0.0255 Omega cm(2) is achieved at 800 degrees C for SCFN-50SDC composite cathode.
Titulo: Characterization of SrCo0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-δ cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For SCFN-xSDC (x = 0, 40, 50, 60) composites, the maximum power densities of single-cells with SCFN-xSDC cathodes on 300 mum thick SDC electrolyte achieve 417, 557, 630 and 517 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Characterization of SrCo0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-δ cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These results indicate that SCFN-50SDC composite is a potential cathode material for application in IT-SOFCs.
